From dea81dcfd3497e75eb23e7543434f88c34289d31 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: "Paul E. McKenney" <paulmck@kernel.org>
Date: Mon, 26 Jun 2023 16:27:02 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] torture: Move torture_shuffle() timeouts to hrtimers
Git-commit: dea81dcfd3497e75eb23e7543434f88c34289d31
Patch-mainline: v6.6-rc1
References: bsc#1219953

In order to gain better race coverage, move the CPU-migration timed
waits in torture_shuffle() to torture_hrtimeout_jiffies().

Signed-off-by: Paul E. McKenney <paulmck@kernel.org>
Signed-off-by: Jiri Wiesner <jwiesner@suse.de>
---
 kernel/torture.c | 4 +++-
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/kernel/torture.c b/kernel/torture.c
index 2c441d5a1bdd..c5311154bc4d 100644
--- a/kernel/torture.c
+++ b/kernel/torture.c
@@ -557,9 +557,11 @@ static void torture_shuffle_tasks(void)
  */
 static int torture_shuffle(void *arg)
 {
+	DEFINE_TORTURE_RANDOM(rand);
+
 	VERBOSE_TOROUT_STRING("torture_shuffle task started");
 	do {
-		schedule_timeout_interruptible(shuffle_interval);
+		torture_hrtimeout_jiffies(shuffle_interval, &rand);
 		torture_shuffle_tasks();
 		torture_shutdown_absorb("torture_shuffle");
 	} while (!torture_must_stop());
